The paper is about a platform for applying reinforcement learning to Flash games, which falls under the category of artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also discusses the performance of the platform, which could be relevant to machine learning (cs.LG) and graphics (cs.GR). Additionally, the platform could have implications for human-computer interaction (cs.HC) and social and information networks (cs.SI) if it leads to the development of more advanced and interactive Flash games.
